response_a:
The error is caused by the fact that you are trying to set the diagonal elements of the decision variable x(i,j) to zero using the autotour equation. However, in GAMS, decision variables must be non-negative, and setting the diagonal elements to zero would violate this constraint.

One way to fix this error is to use a big M constraint to force the diagonal elements to be zero. You can do this by defining a large constant M and then adding the constraint:

x(i,i) <= M for all i

This constraint ensures that the diagonal elements of x(i,j) will be zero, while still allowing the decision variable to be non-negative. Here's the corrected code:

